&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; background-color:#ffffff;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica Neue,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:8pt; color:#333333; background-color:#ffffff;&quot;&gt;Processes or threads that are working together may share common storage that is used to read and write, whether it is located in memory or in a shared file. Race conditions are situations where the final result of an operation on the shared data depends on which process or thread runs precisely when.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
